An alien has kidnapped Matt Damon, not knowing what lengths humanity goes through to retrieve him whenever he goes missing.

The aliens take Matt to their planet, read his mind, and place him in a familiar setting. He is in a cabin in the woods, and autumn leaves flame outside the windows in spite of the dark skies above. In front of him is a bottle of vodka with a blue label, about one-third full.

Matt remembers the abduction, and he also recalls his last thought before the alien knocked him out: "Thank God."

Because Matt was tired.MHe had been tired for a long time.
 He was tired of the movies, the photographers, the false smiles, and the endless grind of having to seem happy. He was tired of the long hours, the constant travel, the constant pressure, and the constant need to be liked.

He wanted out.
He had been thinking about it for a long time, but he had never been able to find the courage to do it.
 But now someone (something?) had seemingly done it for him.

He got up and opened the cabin door. A cool wind shuffled the leaves and flapped his collar.
He walked out of the cabin and into the woods.
 The rising sun turned the sky pink ahead of him. Matt well knew what lengths humanity goes through to retrieve him whenever he goes missing, but good luck finding him now. Because he was never going back.
